This paper deals with medical imaging analysis using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves a novel approach for 3D segmentation, which could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pre-trained models, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
